The effect of global warming may be unavoidable, but it can be hard to comprehend from the comfort of our homes.

However, it becomes painfully clear in this stunning set of images, showing some of the regions most at risk: The Arctic and Antarctica. 

Photographer Camille Seaman has been travelling to areas near both poles for more than a decade, capturing the lives of polar bears and penguins and the melting ice shelves. 

